The paper discusses the problem of learning a model in partially observable environments, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The method proposed involves constructing a hierarchical transition model, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions using visual information to identify different objects in different rooms, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the method to autonomous agents, which is relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
